385,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-24 09:55:23+00:00,38900806,aleju/imgaug,11698516,aleju,,,267961470,338938104,"Can you check whether your input images are really all 32x32x3 and maybe write a minimal working example? I tried the below (similar) code and didn't get any such problem:
```python
from __future__ import print_function
from imgaug import augmenters as iaa
import imgaug as ia

image = ia.quokka(size=(32, 32))

seq = iaa.Sequential([
    iaa.GaussianBlur((0, 0.5)),
    iaa.ContrastNormalization((0.75, 1.5)),
    iaa.AverageBlur(k=(2, 7))
])

for _ in xrange(100):
    image_aug = seq.augment_images([image])[0]
    print(image.shape, image_aug.shape, ""changed"" if image.shape != image_aug.shape else ""OK"")
```

