869,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-28 10:11:21+00:00,48846863,pavoni/pyvera,4487313,pavoni,,,325148349,392483879,"One approach might be to search for the `SUCCESS` string in the comment - and force a change of status if that's the case. I had to do something similar here:-

https://github.com/pavoni/pyvera/blob/master/pyvera/subscribe.py#L70
https://github.com/pavoni/pyvera/blob/master/pyvera/subscribe.py#L75

In this case Vera was saying `STATE_NO_JOB ` which is normally a state you can trust as a final outcome - but in this case there was a comment about sending.

If the `SUCCESS` comment is reliable you can adjust the `VeraLock` logic to something like:
```
if device.__class__.__name__ == 'VeraLock'):
    # VeraLocks don't complete - so force state
    success = comment.find('SUCCESS!') >= 0
    if success and state == STATE_JOB_IN_PROGRESS:
            state = STATE_JOB_DONE
  ```

If this works then we'd be able to trust the subscription state, remove the extra thread, and not have lock switches in HA bounce.
",{},OWNER,User,False
871,IssueCommentEvent,2017-03-21 10:09:51+00:00,48846863,pavoni/pyvera,4487313,pavoni,,,215268519,288032076,"It's important the position is correct, because if it isn't - then HA will enable / disable the buttons incorrectly.

Will double check my cover at the weekend - but I'm pretty sure mine works (I use a Fibaro FGR-222). What blind controller are you using?

The vera commands for `position` and `open/close/stop` are different. However (if I remember correctly) my controller sends position updates in response to the `open/close/stop` commands, so I don't default the state in the code after you click open/close.

It's quite possible your controller doesn't send position updates, so needs me to default them. The only tricky part of this is what happens when you click `stop`!

Can you turn up the logging level to `debug` in pyvera? (https://home-assistant.io/components/logger/). This should trace the commands sent - and the status updated that come back. This should give us more clues about what is happening.",{},,User,False
