1342,IssueCommentEvent,2015-05-26 01:08:56+00:00,19361153,tdryer/hangups,950506,simon-weber,,,80003966,105345541,"Well, it's definitely not going to be that simple, haha. The reason I missed this the first time around is that the android client doesn't seem to hit client-channel over http, and I was just looking at the http layer. They probably use gcm instead, which probably has an implementation directly on top of the transport layer. I know very little about how gcm works, but there's a good chance that there's an auth blocker there (ie, sso with no option for oauth). I'll see if I can confirm that.

