1596,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-10 03:08:19+00:00,27283062,ktbyers/netmiko,15805672,chesean,,,321276403,387938479,"Hi Kirk,

I finally get it working by modifying utilities.py in netmiko package. See my modification with utilities.py below.

If I use original template_dir = os.environ[‘NET_TEXTFSM’] and I set Python console environment variables: NET_TEXTFSM =/Users/ABC/Sites/project2/ntc-templates/templates, by debugging, I see template_dir becomes ""/Users/ABC/Sites/project2/ntc-templates/templates /templates’, so there’s one extra space there and one templates (red) there. To fix that, I use str.strip(os.environ[‘NET_TEXTFSM’]) to remove the extra space in the end, and set environment variables to be 'NET_TEXTFSM=/Users/Sean/Sites/project2/ntc-templates’. 

After these changes, the ‘template_dir’ becomes ""/Users/ABC/Sites/project2/ntc-templates/templates” which reflect the correct directory of ntc-template location.

def get_template_dir():
    """"""Find and return the ntc-templates/templates dir.""""""
    try:
        template_dir = str.strip(os.environ['NET_TEXTFSM’]) <—— My new code
        #template_dir = os.environ['NET_TEXTFSM’]<—— Original code
        index = os.path.join(template_dir, 'index')

        if not os.path.isfile(index):
            # Assume only base ./ntc-templates specified
            template_dir = os.path.join(template_dir, 'templates')
    except KeyError:
        # Construct path ~/ntc-templates/templates
        home_dir = os.path.expanduser(""~"")
        template_dir = os.path.join(home_dir, 'ntc-templates', 'templates')

    index = os.path.join(template_dir, 'index')
    
    if not os.path.isdir(template_dir) or not os.path.isfile(index):
        msg = """"""
Valid ntc-templates not found, please install https://github.com/networktocode/ntc-templates
and then set the NET_TEXTFSM environment variable to point to the ./ntc-templates/templates
directory.""""""

Not sure if this is best solution. but it works fine so far.

Thanks,
Sean

