settings?

export http_proxy=http://proxy.vort.se:8080
export https_proxy=http://username:password@proxy.incolume.com.br:8080

On Wed, Jan 27, 2016 at 7:11 AM, Garmahis666 <notifications@github.com>
wrote:

> I began to test the robot on a computer connected to the Internet through
> a proxy. And the request
> import telepot
> bot = telepot.Bot ('***** PUT YOUR TOKEN HERE *****')
> bot.getMe ()
> I get the appropriate error.
> I looked implementation method.
> def getMe (self):
> r = requests.post (self._methodurl ('getMe'), timeout =
> self._http_timeout)
> return self._parse (r)
> The simplest thing you can do is write:
> def getMe (self):
> r = requests.post (self._methodurl ('getMe'), timeout =
> self._http_timeout, proxies = urllib.request.getproxies ())
> return self._parse (r)
> so we work at least take those proxy settings that are registered in the
> system.
>
> —
> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub
> <https://github.com/nickoala/telepot/issues/21#issuecomment-175499917>.
>
",{},,User,False
