2143,IssueCommentEvent,2016-04-25 15:56:39+00:00,9289343,svinota/pyroute2,814602,svinota,,,150866955,214415192,"I'm not sure the freeze is caused by the library's activity. But when the netlink parser (in async mode, as in IPDB, it checks timers) detects such freezes, it automatically tries to reprioritize the caching thread — to avoid possible netlink socket breakdown (it is required by the kernel to read all the messages from the socket, otherwise you will have to restart the socket — and thus all the database).

The log warning tells that there are still 14 not parsed messages in the parser queue, which is by 14 more than on the previous measurement time, so it suspends the main thread (which calls `get()`) for 0.1 seconds to give the caching thread a chance to manage with those messages.",{},,User,False
