2718,IssueCommentEvent,2012-01-25 15:28:08+00:00,2675994,jamescasbon/PyVCF,97495,jamescasbon,,,2965813,3652492,"On Wed, Jan 25, 2012 at 3:06 PM, Aaron Quinlan <
reply@reply.github.com
> wrote:

> Sorry, I don't follow what you are asking me to do.  Can you provide a
> more detailed explanation/example?  I have no experience with Sphinx.


Just use '#:' to document the attribute.  I have patched your code to do
this:
https://github.com/jamescasbon/PyVCF/blob/master/vcf.py#L350

Long explanation:
autodoc is a sphinx extension that picks out docstrings from modules,
classes and methods.  Unfortunately, class *attributes* do not have
docstrings.  To work around this, you can add documentation to attributes
like this:
http://sphinx.pocoo.org/ext/autodoc.html#directive-autoattribute
with either '#:' before the attribute or a docstring on the next line.

This allows me to auto generate API documentation, which will soo be
available at http://pyvcf.readthedocs.org/


-- 

James Casbon

Population Genetics - http://www.populationgenetics.com/
james.casbon@populationgenetics.com
