2763,IssueCommentEvent,2015-01-18 13:46:07+00:00,1938370,Mottie/tablesorter,136959,Mottie,,,49769266,70408844,"Hmm, oh... the delay in adding the processing class name to the headers is only used when  the `sortBegin` event is fired ([line 1155](https://github.com/Mottie/tablesorter/blob/master/js/jquery.tablesorter.js#L1155)).

The code you are interested in is in the pager. At the top of the `getAjax` function ([line 714 of the pager widget](https://github.com/Mottie/tablesorter/blob/master/js/widgets/widget-pager.js#L714)) - it checks the `config.showProcessing` option setting, then calls the code to add the icons.

```js
if (c.showProcessing) {
	ts.isProcessing(table, true); // show loading icon
}
```

Then in the `renderAjax` function ([line 680 of the pager widget](https://github.com/Mottie/tablesorter/blob/master/js/widgets/widget-pager.js#L680)) is the check to remove the processing class names:

```js
if (c.showProcessing) {
	ts.isProcessing(table); // remove loading icon
}
```",{},,User,False
2765,IssueCommentEvent,2015-03-24 21:46:40+00:00,1938370,Mottie/tablesorter,136959,Mottie,,,58813484,85706664,"Hi @seemikehack!

Only the combined `jquery.tablesorter.widgets.js` file includes an UMD wrapper. That file contains the following widgets:

* storage
* uitheme
* columns
* filter
* stickyHeaders
* resizable
* saveSort

If you only need the uitheme widget, then create a [custom build](https://github.com/Mottie/tablesorter/wiki/Customize#custom-build).

I'll add an option to the custom build, so you can name the output file whatever you want.",{},,User,False
