2780,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-18 07:07:59+00:00,1938370,Mottie/tablesorter,15000719,tarifrudrapur,,,223059752,302320016,"@Mottie 
Sorry for they delay in reply.
I found the solution for that.
The issue was in the custom parser


Here is the code

```
        $.tablesorter.addParser({ 
                    // set a unique id 
                    id: 'status',
                    is: function(s) {
                        // return true so this parser is auto detected 
                        return false; 
                    },  
                    format: function(s) { 
                        // format your data for normalization 
                        for(var i=0; i<getTypeList.length;i++){
                            if(s == getTypeList[i])
                                return i;
                        }
                        return -1;
                    }, 
                    // set type, either numeric or text 
                    type: 'numeric' 
                });
```
",{},,User,False
