self.assertTrue( (6,6) in nn)
self.assertTrue( (5,5) in nn)
self.assertTrue( (5,6) in nn)
self.assertTrue( (6,5) in nn)

The point(4,4) is missing. The Euclidean distance between (5,5) and (4,4) is 1.414214 and hence should be included if the radius param is 2.5.

I've made a pull request for this bug.",{},NONE,User,False
