3970,IssueCommentEvent,2017-04-15 14:34:23+00:00,2069170,kraiz/django-crontab,634934,kraiz,,,221802878,294297072,"Hey, if you want to run your command via

    python manage.py check_celery_status

it should be in `myapp.management.commands.check_celery_status`. If you can run it this way, you should be able to define this settings:

    CRONJOBS = [
        ('* * * * *', 'django.core.management.call_command', ['check_celery_status'], {}, '>> /tmp/check_celery_status.log'),
    ]

Then activate it via:

    python manage.py crontab add

...and watch `/tmp/check_celery_status.log` which should contain the output of you command.",{},,User,False
