4548,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-09 15:31:36+00:00,58694159,timdaman/check_docker,4292968,timdaman,,,301385267,371845918,"The Docker documentation says 

> A tag name must be valid ASCII and may contain lowercase and uppercase letters, digits, underscores, periods and dashes. A tag name may not start with a period or a dash and may contain a maximum of 128 characters.

The first grouping ensure the tag starts with a valid letter. The problem is the second grouping should not be modified by a '+', it should be modified by a '*'. That way single letter tags can be supported.
I just pushed that tweak.

Your fix works but has the side effect of ignoring the spec. The spec is actually pretty complex so I have a couple edge case too; I don't handle '__' specially in image names and I can't handle registry hostnames that don't contain '.'. I plan on fixing those once I have all the previously known issues resolved.",{},OWNER,User,False
