4709,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-27 03:50:47+00:00,91844116,ericvsmith/dataclasses,1026649,ncoghlan,,,276826253,347072339,"I agree with the idea of ""protocol method name without the prefix & suffix"" being a good baseline convention. That way it's only the ordered comparison parameter name that's up for discussion.

By the baseline convention, since these parameter names are also method names, it's actually OK for them to be verbs. And if we ever decided it made sense to bring back support for cmp-style ordering implementations (perhaps as an alternative input format for `functools.total_ordering`), then `def __order__(self, other):` would be a reasonable name for that.",{},NONE,User,False
