4728,IssueCommentEvent,2016-05-25 04:34:38+00:00,5430433,jjjake/internetarchive,4283973,ewen-naos-nz,,,156179666,221470870,"FWIW, I've figured out why they ended up in the `opensource` collection: [according to the documentation it is the default collection](https://internetarchive.readthedocs.io/en/latest/metadata.html#collection).  So nothing to do with the subject tags.

It *may* make sense to continue that default for one-off uploads (although personally I'd lean towards ""explicit is better than implicit"" for things that cannot easily be changed later).  But in the spreadsheet/multiple-create case I definitely think it'd be best to only *create* with an explicit specification of `collection` (and `mediatype`) to stay consistent with the principle of least surprise.  In the spreadsheet case it doesn't take much extra effort to specify the `collection` and `mediatype` for each item (even if making the spreadsheet by hand).

Ewen",{},,User,False
