5796,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-19 13:25:17+00:00,35990433,kata198/AdvancedHTMLParser,8461115,kata198,,,229557858,302701937,"What is this?

Almost all your changes are adding .bak files..... and AdvancedHTMLParser is already compatible with both python 2 and python3.. hence the following quoted code and example of me running the unit tests in both python2 and python3.

Are you actually getting any specific error? I do use this on python3 on the daily, but there may be some obscure usage somewhere that's broke? I have tested it on python 3.4, 3.5, and 3.6. Python 3.0 to 3.3 should not be used for anything anywhere.. but they would probably work as well.

I'm going to deny this merge request, of course, but if you DO have a specific error you can show me I can fix it. 2to3 is not a very good tool, it's more of a quick ""python3 now!"" tool. For example, you've converted EVERY generator into an explicit list, which some corner case may fix but in general will very much hurt performance or even break code.

I see you have a TON of these kind of pulls... are you just a robot that does this, or are you a real person?


**Example python2/python3 code** (which your patch would break, of course, making it NOT work with python2 and not any better on python3):
