5953,IssueCommentEvent,2015-12-23 07:27:30+00:00,8794780,kvesteri/wtforms-components,3326999,tvuotila,,,123507184,166822499,"What if form edits an existing object? `form._obj` is needed for finding out the object currently being edited.

As in [documentation example](http://wtforms-components.readthedocs.org/en/latest/index.html#unique-validator) you should inherit your form from [ModelForm](https://github.com/kvesteri/wtforms-components/blob/80284f920dd7432a27e43695a370901c8305bd8f/wtforms_components/__init__.py#L71). That way you have the `form._obj` set in `def __init__`. I think this could be emphasized more.

