6175,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-13 19:03:27+00:00,51490769,bshillingford/python-torchfile,2326749,bshillingford,,,228461860,301268192,"You can see its properties with .keys() or tab completion, like any other
dictionary. A TorchObject is a lua table emulated in Python (so that all
objects, including non-hashable ones, can be keys). If in lua you accessed
the property containing your torch tensor with obj['a']['b'][123], you'd do
the same in python to get the numpy array.
",{},,User,False
