6192,IssueCommentEvent,2017-08-21 04:38:48+00:00,5981620,goinnn/django-multiselectfield,597113,blag,,,251512554,323644718,"This is more of a Python/Django problem than an issue with this particular package, so I'll be closing this issue.

Think about when the code that assigns into `choices` is run. It's only run once, when the server starts up. There's no way to restrict the available choices in the model like you want to do. You will have to create a many-to-many relation to `Subject` objects and restrict them in your forms. See this SO post for more:

https://stackoverflow.com/a/3420588",{},,User,False
