6205,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-30 03:58:47+00:00,39119843,miguelgrinberg/python-socketio,2715854,miguelgrinberg,,,277987890,348075985,"If you are asking about exceptions on the client side, that depends on the client that you are using. 

For the server, when a client disconnects you are going to get a `'disconnect'` event. If you have a handler for this event, then your function can do whatever is necessary for this client that is gone.

Note that the Socket.IO protocol includes reconnection attempts, so as soon as the client is back within the wifi range it is going to attempt a new connection, for which you will get a new `'connect'` event.",{},OWNER,User,False
