6229,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-07 03:11:37+00:00,106152498,snoack/flake8-per-file-ignores,1525,snoack,,,302886267,371008107,"We cannot use the `glob` module but have to use `fnmatch` as explained in https://github.com/snoack/flake8-per-file-ignores/issues/1#issuecomment-335046937. Therefore `*` is already matching across directory boundaries, as explained [here](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/18341848/fnmatch-and-recursive-path-match-with#answer-18341937). That means `*/__init__.py` would match `a/__init__.py` and `a/b/__init__py` but not `__init__.py` (on the top-level).

Admittedly, these semantics are kinda confusing, impractical and inconsistent, but I'm not going to implement my own glob pattern parser (and again the `glob` module isn't an appropriate option here).

Anyway, in order to match files with the same (or similar) name, regardless of their location, hindsight, it might have been a better idea to require an explicit trailing `/` to imply the root (like in `.gitignore`). However, at the current point this would be a slightly breaking change.

@kvas-it and @The-Compiler, what do you think?",{},OWNER,User,False
