6294,IssueCommentEvent,2015-06-29 14:32:25+00:00,10674033,marcgibbons/django-rest-swagger,1450630,pedrospdc,,,91811171,116705450,"Found it on http://stackoverflow.com/questions/8864628/empty-docstrings-when-running-django-piston-docs-under-nginx

uWSGI is starting up the interpreter in way equivalent to -OO option to Python command line. This second level of optimisation removes doc strings.

-OO    : remove doc-strings in addition to the -O optimizations
Change:

--optimize 2
to:

--optimize 1
",{},,User,False
