6639,IssueCommentEvent,2015-09-22 18:58:28+00:00,30386388,box/box-python-sdk,1150978,jmoldow,23900,box,107757744,142385674,"The event should tell you the id and type of the item. I'm not familiar with tag creation events in particular, but I'd expect the JSON to contain something like this: ``{..., 'id': '1234', 'type': 'file', ...}`` or ``{..., 'id': '5678', 'type': 'folder', ...}``. Then in the case of the file, you can do ``tags = client.file(file_id).get(fields=['tags']).tags``.

Or you can do both of them, with something like

```python
item_id = ... # from the event
item_type = ... # 'file' or 'folder', from the event
item = getattr(client, item_type)(item_id).get(fields=['tags'])  # An instance of Item. Will actually be either an instance of Folder or File.
tags = item.tags
```",{},,User,False
