6887,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-02 17:55:25+00:00,24774658,boto/boto3,1010634,stealthycoin,327752,boto,233232321,305865543,"Why do you say it is inconsistent? They are different, one is in the user defined metadata which is always prefixed with `x-amz-meta-` so it doesn't collide with any other names. The other is for setting the content type.

Our `extra_args` parameters map to headers outlined here:
http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/RESTObjectPUT.html

Metadata holds no special meaning and is simply to store your own meta data. The others have defined meanings in the API defined in that link above.",{},,User,False
