7034,IssueCommentEvent,2015-11-06 17:32:00+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,430360,jchauncey,6117407,deis,112237868,154479940,"Counting is far more complex because I will have to keep the state of every container in which I see at least 1 die event. While some stream processors are capable of doing this, other tools we are evaluating make this more difficult. 

If the container was in an error state and dies then it is much easier to say we no longer are receiving stats for that container and we alert on that case. It also is much easier to capture the cause of the container dying when we are not always destroying the container when it fails. Eventually, it will stop removing the container and its last state will be around for me to determine what the caused the exit.
",{},,User,False
