7085,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-08 20:20:11+00:00,14348727,hzdg/django-enumfields,6073918,NovaDev94,777793,hzdg,217289691,299979117,"Hi @jbowman1107, this is taken from my production codebase

```python
class Status(Enum):
    PENDING = 'pending'
    PROCESSING = 'processing'
    DELIVERING = 'delivering'
    SERVING = 'serving'
    DONE = 'done'
    DECLINED = 'declined'
    CANCELED = 'canceled'
    ERROR = 'error'

class Order(models.Model):
    status = EnumField(Status, default=Status.PENDING)
```

And it works with `?status=pending`. Please note that it use the Enum value (not the label or so).  
",{},,User,False
