7121,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-24 23:07:42+00:00,2866041,kivy/python-for-android,380158,frmdstryr,1266152,kivy,258131455,339163114,"Is there any reason p4a can't use something like [entry_points](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/774824/explain-python-entry-points#9615473) built into setuptools to allow version specific recipes to be installed independently of p4a? 

Using this, each recipe could be in it's own repo and you could install a specific version with pip.
