7342,IssueCommentEvent,2016-12-07 20:14:38+00:00,54980593,pypa/setuptools,308610,jaraco,647025,pypa,183524944,265560581,"> Does this have to be another call?

Not necessarily.

> What about adding installed=False parameter?

My opinion is that a boolean parameter is [generally an anti-pattern](http://blog.iannelson.systems/back-to-basics-on-the-use-and-abuse-of-the-humble-boolean/), though it really depends on the implementation. If the two functions are essentially doing the same thing with the selector happening deep in a loop, then the burden of copy-pasting most of that logic into two separate functions is worse than having a boolean parameter. The best implementation, however, will have good separation of concerns and without repetition.

That said, I'd be happy with any implementation that works and has tests, and we can refine the approach later if necessary.",{},,User,False
7348,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-01 15:07:57+00:00,54980593,pypa/setuptools,1377457,pganssle,647025,pypa,319127576,385694560,"I weakly disagree with keeping this in unless we're actually going to start using `--flake8` in the CI. This is not required for running the tests and anyone who *wants* to use `--flake8` can always run `pip install pytest-flake8`.

I also don't really think we should be complicating the build environment to support old versions of `pip`. This one was easy enough, but soon enough we'll start seeing incompatibilities with transitive dependencies, so we'll have to start actively adding and pinning specific versions of transitive dependencies. `Python-Requires` should be enough.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
