7354,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-14 11:06:36+00:00,54980593,pypa/setuptools,6939968,anthrotype,647025,pypa,232185901,344224679,"`build_clib` is useful for example when you are wrapping an existing C library and would like to build a static library using only distutils/setuptools and link that to your extension module.

I believe `develop` should call `build_clib` if the distribution has any c libraries, just before it calls `build_ext`.

And yes, the distutils `build` command invokes `build_clib` before `build_ext`, the latter are both present in the right order inside the `build` command's `sub_commands` attribute:
https://github.com/python/cpython/blob/e1d62e0b7cc842d6b75b4d480391f4a94e503255/Lib/distutils/command/build.py#L153-L157",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
