8108,IssueCommentEvent,2016-03-02 14:19:01+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,38393,msarahan,6392739,conda,112721937,191253884,"@ilanschnell 

> What is the motivation behind renaming CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV?

Never mind, I misspoke.  I renamed things back to CONDA_DEFAULT_ENV in https://github.com/msarahan/conda/commit/c94063cc33e0f77d49e34463a12cd1f7faca26c2

> Why is psutil now a dependency?

psutil is necessary to determine what the parent shell is.  This is in turn necessary to make conda behave appropriately (slash behavior and help output) for shells other than cmd.exe on Windows.

> What are the Windows to Unix path conversion functions used for?

Primarily for test_activate.py, but they see some use in symlinking also.  The main reason why is that os.path.join always joins with platform-native slashes, but these are inappropriate for bash shells on Windows.

> How exactly does the symlinking of conda into environments change?

On Windows, bat files are created in environments that call back to the activate scripts in the root environment.  Bash on windows uses ln in a subprocess call.  Powershell is currently not implemented.  Linux/Mac have not changed.

> How did this PR get so large to being with?

This PR is more than a year old.  It was originally proposed as https://github.com/conda/conda/pull/913/ in September 2014.  It required fixing after the conda-conda env split. @wulmer proposed https://github.com/conda/conda/pull/1707, and I created this PR to fix his code a bit.  At that point, Aaron had left, and had left us with no Windows CI, because he tied Appveyor to his personal account with Appveyor.  This PR thus included some changes to fix Appveyor, because this PR made drastic changes to Windows.  (those have now been removed, because Kale fixed them independently of this PR)  We had the Anaconda 2.4.0 release, and this PR got lost.  Then @MaxNoe submitted his change to add bash support on windows.  I invited him to submit it here, because it really should depend/build on the work that @wulmer did.  If @wulmer's work had been merged earlier, then the bash stuff could have been separate.  The ""bash stuff"" includes all of the path translation and psutil addition, as well as fixes to conda required to fix the invalid assumption that when sys.platform==win32, then windows paths are always what you're dealing with.

> Why wasn't it possible to create a few smaller (and more manageable) PRs instead?

This question is perhaps better answered with another question: why wasn't it possible to merge this PR in any of its earlier iterations?  This PR has snowballed because it hasn't been merged, and subsequent development (such as the bash support on Windows) depends on the changes made earlier.  PRs that depend on PRs are difficult to manage at best.",{},,User,False
8110,IssueCommentEvent,2017-08-08 13:56:34+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,1042804,mingwandroid,6392739,conda,248697504,320963587,"In your `PATH`, this entry is incorrect `C:\Program Files\MySQL\MySQL Server 5.7\bin；`, specifically the semicolon at the end is not a semicolon (ascii), but instead a fullwidth semicolon (non-ascii).

You should be able to just delete the last (thing that looks like a) semicolon from your Windows `PATH`.",{},,User,False
