8115,IssueCommentEvent,2018-02-22 22:37:50+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,1042804,mingwandroid,6392739,conda,299175052,367846915,"Different people do different things?

While in the past the `Anaconda Distribution` `defaults` packages were built from our own recipes, they are now built from recipes that are forked from `conda-forge`'s since it scales better to have the community curate them and in many cases `conda-forge` has involvement of domain experts or of upstream package authors and/or maintainers.

Our hope is to get the recipes and thus the packages as close as possible.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
8116,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-08 17:58:38+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,1418419,kalefranz,6392739,conda,164572250,231428939,"I wasn't aware of the constructor and cas-installer files. I plan to deprecate environment.yml in a planned and controlled way. The new file will be condaenv.yml, which will be a strict subset of kapsel.yml. At least those are my thoughts right now. 

> On Jul 8, 2016, at 11:54 AM, Sean Ross-Ross <notifications@github.com> wrote:
> 
> Problems
> 
> Too many files
> 
> Conda and anaconda have a growing number of files that can be used for different purposes, but achieve the basic functionality of creating or specifying an environment.
> 
> Some formats add to this core, but they all share the same base.
> 
> Command	Instals packages	Channel support	pip support	project support	platform specificity	different requirement syntax
> command line	✅	✅	✅	✅	⛔	-
> requirements.txt	✅	⛔	⛔	⛔	⛔	-
> environment.yaml	✅	✅	✅	⛔	⛔	-
> project.yaml | kapsel.yaml	✅	✅	✅	✅	⛔	-
> constructor.yaml	✅	✅	⛔	⛔	⛔	-
> cas-installer.yaml	✅	✅	⛔	⛔	⛔	-
> meta.yaml	✅	✅	⛔	⛔	✅	💀
> Notes
> 
> meta.yaml
> ✅ can use requirements.txt if found
> Possible Solutions
> 
> Lets standardize.
> 
> As we move forward we should think about how adding new file formats and definitions affects the conda ecosystem. Are we going to have an ever growing list of file formats? Or should we deprecate a few in a planned and controlled way?
> 
> —
> You are receiving this because you are subscribed to this thread.
