8163,IssueCommentEvent,2016-08-05 17:43:40+00:00,547504,geopy/geopy,7433104,micahcochran,1385808,geopy,101422207,237915448,"I like the idea of the patch.    Shouldn't this patch atleast have a vincenty class that issues a [deprecation warning](https://docs.python.org/2/library/warnings.html), so as to not entirely break the API?  

That could just be a dummy class that with and __init__ function issues the DeprecationWarning, that is derived from geodesic.

Something like this (this is pseudocode):
```Python
import warnings

class vincenty(geodesic):
    def __init__(self, *args, **kwargs):
        warnings.warn('Replace class distance.vincenty with class geodesic', DeprecationWarning)
        super(geodesic, self).__init__(*args, **kwargs)
```",{},,User,False
