8279,IssueCommentEvent,2016-11-07 16:35:56+00:00,35100117,neo4j/neo4j-python-driver,4190164,zhenlineo,201120,neo4j,178735854,258886716,"Hi,

I think you might consider adding error handling on the session rather than connection. If you keep the `driver` around, then you could easily create a new session from the driver. If you retry your statement in another session after the server already restated, then the statement will run successfully in this new session.

Is there any reason that you want to keep the session around? I do not think you could re-establish a connection for a session. But a new connection will be established when you obtain a new session from the driver.

Cheer,
Zhen",{},,User,False
