8551,IssueCommentEvent,2016-02-04 16:46:25+00:00,20493628,G-Node/nixpy,2040,gicmo,574778,G-Node,131402538,179939677,"Ah, python, always great fun. `DataArray`s (or better `DataSet`s) don't actually explicitly support the iteration protocol (i.e. `__iter__`). Mostly because it is probably not a good idea to go down to the file for every single number. We have a `__len__` and `__getitem__` which I guess makes the range based for loop work. To make it fully work though we would have to throw a `IndexError` in the [DataSet](https://github.com/G-Node/nixpy/blob/master/nix/data_array.py#L112) I guess. A bit of overhead, but why not ...",{},,User,False
