8650,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-02 15:04:20+00:00,3342046,RDFLib/rdflib,617997,aaronhelton,1401847,RDFLib,228736828,305814479,"The function that fails here is split_uri from namsepace.py

`>>> from rdflib import *
INFO:rdflib:RDFLib Version: 4.2.2
>>> from rdflib.namespace import split_uri
>>> ns = Namespace('http://some.uri/foo/')
>>> t = ns['1234']
>>> split_uri(t)
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""<stdin>"", line 1, in <module>
  File ""/home/ec2-user/projects/venv_rdflib_test/local/lib/python3.4/site-packages/rdflib/namespace.py"", line 502, in split_uri
    raise Exception(""Can't split '%s'"" % uri)
Exception: Can't split 'http://some.uri/foo/1234'
>>> t
rdflib.term.URIRef('http://some.uri/foo/1234')`

The function is necessary for the Graph to run the qname function, which ends up calling split_uri via the compute_qname function:
`>>> from rdflib.namespace import NamespaceManager
>>> g = Graph()
>>> nsm = NamespaceManager(g)
>>> nsm.qname(t)
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""<stdin>"", line 1, in <module>
  File ""/home/ec2-user/projects/venv_rdflib_test/local/lib/python3.4/site-packages/rdflib/namespace.py"", line 294, in qname
    prefix, namespace, name = self.compute_qname(uri)
  File ""/home/ec2-user/projects/venv_rdflib_test/local/lib/python3.4/site-packages/rdflib/namespace.py"", line 330, in compute_qname
    namespace, name = split_uri(uri)
  File ""/home/ec2-user/projects/venv_rdflib_test/local/lib/python3.4/site-packages/rdflib/namespace.py"", line 502, in split_uri
    raise Exception(""Can't split '%s'"" % uri)
Exception: Can't split 'http://some.uri/foo/1234'
`

This works fine after I make the change linked upthread:
`>>> from rdflib import *
INFO:rdflib:RDFLib Version: 4.2.2
>>> from rdflib.namespace import split_uri, NamespaceManager
>>> ns = Namespace('http://some.uri/foo/')
>>> t = ns['1234']
>>> g = Graph()
>>> nsm = NamespaceManager(g)
>>> nsm.qname(t)
'ns1:1234'
`

Hope that helps. ",{},,User,False
