    m.def(""selective_func"", [](py::array_t<std::complex<float>, py::array::c_style>) { return ""Complex float branch taken.""; });
```

It's not actually very numpy.h-specific, more generally - if we fail in object creation/casting early, we have exception data but we can't do overloads; if we fail later, overloads work, but exception info is lost. I don't know, maybe I'm missing something :)",{},,User,False
