to tell pybind to never delete them when the Python wrapper gets garbage collected.  It's trivially easy to cause a memory leak (just construct an `A` without giving it to a `B`--including, for example, an exception occuring (even if caught) between initialization and handing it off to the B), but it looks like what you're looking for.",{},MEMBER,User,False
