9733,IssueCommentEvent,2018-02-17 15:27:42+00:00,38581626,pybind/pybind11,4459524,jagerman,17565521,pybind,297519930,366448478,"The issue is with:

```C++
std::shared_ptr<Ancestor> CreateChild() { return std::make_shared<Child>(); }
```
In order for pybind to deal with shared pointers, you need to tell it when binding the class to use shared pointers rather than the default `unique_ptr`:

```C++
    py::class_<Ancestor, std::shared_ptr<Ancestor>>(m, ""Ancestor"")
    // ... definitions
```

If I make that change, your example works as expected (without a segfault):

```Python
>>> import i1284
>>> c = i1284.create_child()
>>> c.name
'Child'
>>> # Ctrl-D here exits cleanly
```",{},MEMBER,User,False
