9861,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-11 16:14:32+00:00,1953389,stripe/stripe-python,926355,louischatriot,856813,stripe,313381461,380509917,"Ooooook so after some more testing this does seem like a bug in the API actually :)

The code above fails because it tries to modify the `legal_entity` in two different ways: through an account token (the `first_name` field) and through a direct modification (for `additional_owners`). So this code does empty `additional_owners`:
```python
legal_entity_data = { 'first_name': 'something', 'additional_owners': { 0: { 'first_name': 'LLL' } } }
account_token = stripe.Token.create( account = { 'legal_entity': legal_entity_data, 'tos_shown_and_accepted': True })
stripe_account = stripe.Account.create(type = 'custom', country = 'FR', account_token = account_token.id)

stripe_account.legal_entity.additional_owners = None
stripe_account.save()
stripe_account = stripe.Account.retrieve(stripe_account['id'])   # Should be idempotent but just in case
assert(len(stripe_account['legal_entity']['additional_owners']) == 0)
```

I think the issue is in the API as I could reproduce the behavior with curl: `curl https://api.stripe.com/v1/accounts/acct_1CFlVaFhmtJOxl3R    -u MY_KEY:   -d legal_entity[additional_owners]= -d account_token=ct_1CFlVdDapaWG7UYcsXRnjAIZ`
",{},NONE,User,False
