10043,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-11 17:40:24+00:00,83072729,CartoDB/cartoframes,12551177,michellemho,1799254,CartoDB,222541708,300863622,"More details!

In this dataset, there is an ""end year"" column (integer) that indicates the death year of the artist. If an artist hasn't died or doesn't have an end year, the value is 0. A conversion in Postgres to datetime format (I'm guessing) is taking that year = 0 and changing it to `1-01-01T00:00:00Z`, which is not a valid datetime format according to Pandas:

http://pandas-docs.github.io/pandas-docs-travis/timeseries.html#timestamp-limitations

I think a solution for this issues needs to properly converting the PostgreSQL datetime type to the a valid Pandas datetime type that does not use `pandas.tslib.cast_to_nanoseconds`... I will look into this!

