10136,IssueCommentEvent,2015-09-01 22:31:53+00:00,23924195,Lasagne/Lasagne,417568,craffel,11752110,Lasagne,104363087,136882094,"> 2 sounds the least 'invasive' (we just need to add a line or two), and we can add a comment as well explaining the motivation.

Yes, it also raises a broader ""parameter validation"" question, e.g. to what extent should we verify that the supplied parameters to functions are the correct type, try to cast them when they aren't, and then throw helpful errors when they can't be cast?  That ends up being more than a line or two though, something like:

```Python
if not isinstance(beta2, float):
    try:
        beta2 = float(beta2)
    except:
        raise ValueError('beta2 must be a float, but {} was supplied'.format(beta2))
```
Of course, we could omit the first line as well as the try/except, depending on whether we are OK with people figuring out what the exception caused by `beta2 = float(beta2)` means by themselves.",{},,User,False
10138,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-15 15:11:56+00:00,23924195,Lasagne/Lasagne,629706,f0k,11752110,Lasagne,228607908,308767718,"> we are willing to contribute more to Lasagne, specially for the issues that would help the release of Lasagne

That's great! I'll also be able to contribute more myself when I've finished my thesis (probably in a month), but help for releasing 0.2 would be greatly appreciated. It's taking much longer than anticipated.

> Do you have any suggestions where I can help you?

In general, the issues/PRs to be addressed for 0.2 are listed in this milestone:
https://github.com/Lasagne/Lasagne/milestone/2
I just went through the list and moved some to 0.3 that would just be nice to have, but are not essential. Also I tagged all with ""documentation"" that only require documentation changes, and one with ""easy"".
Most of the issues are relatively straightforward. Two are meant to straighten the interface before setting it in stone: #719, #399. Those will require some thought/discussion.
Feel free to browse the list and take anything you want -- just leave a post that you're working on it, and please ask if anything is unclear. Looking forward to your contributions!",{},,User,False
