10546,IssueCommentEvent,2016-12-12 22:27:46+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,6389140,thctlo,17889013,certbot,194709599,266573338,"Hi,
I read the thead here and i would say, i love an automation option. 

I was thinking about suche thing this evening, and dont know how but ended on this thread :-)
I was thinking about a vhost setup with mod macro which redirects all FQDN as vhost defained to ssl. 
and this done with certbot on a debian 8 server. 
My idea was with the some of the code of this ssltester : [testssl.sh](https://github.com/drwetter/testssl.sh) to automate testing, so the config can be automaticly checked. 
I write a bit in bash, python bit out of my leage, i can read it a bit. the ideas was.
i wanted to write a script so i setup apache with http mod_macro defined defaults. 
and let certbot create all ssl certs based on the ouputs of my apache vhost config test, so certbot can get all fqdn and aliases, to create the correct cert and reload apache, test ssl with the testssl.sh tool, for all site that are tested ok, enable forced redirect to ssl. 
for the failed, i create an site that shows the domain tested in the site with a message that the ssl install failed. ( and if needed mail admin ), or disable ssl redirect. 

