10547,IssueCommentEvent,2017-01-23 22:29:58+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,3881885,terrycloth,17889013,certbot,202278374,274638492,"I read #3824, which refers to #2305, which refers to #3615. That last thread was a little confusing to me, but these all seem to drift further and further away from my original point. #3824 asks for a more specific error message, but was closed without getting one. #2305 asks for a way to specify which domains to renew, but was closed in favor of #3615, which does not even implement that, as far as I can tell...

My original point was that the `domains` line in `cli.ini` makes it easier to create certificates the first time but breaks renewing them: If the renew command is only ever going to just renew all active certificates, maybe it could simply ignore the `domains` config line? Renewing all active certs is what I want, and it seems silly to have to edit your certbot config file before creating domain certificates and then again afterward. This sort of global configuration file for an application normally still works for all actions the app is able to do.

The workaround in the meanwhile I guess is to use `certbot certonly` instead. That works --- *if* you can use renewal hooks on the certonly command. But from reading the documentation, I'm not sure that you can.",{},,User,False
