10704,IssueCommentEvent,2018-01-13 05:21:53+00:00,15381974,groveco/django-sql-explorer,8053478,gosborn,3093407,groveco,258353140,357411205,"I think using slugify is great! I've updated the PR to use it. From our use, it appears that most reports are titled something like ""Attorney Signup Report"", so ""attorney-signup-report"" is very reasonable. In cases where slugify would remove a special character, i.e. ""Attorney/Paralegal Signup Report"", the formatting is a little less desirable (""attorneyparalegal-signup-report""), but I too am wary of regular expressions - I think using slugify more than makes up for that less desirable formatting (seems to be an edge case anyways) in code-cleanliness and maintenance. Thanks for the suggestion!",{},NONE,User,False
