10904,IssueCommentEvent,2017-03-07 21:16:08+00:00,17380426,libnano/primer3-py,2595010,benpruitt,9573677,libnano,212482278,284861680,"I think that post was just referring to the salt correction parameters (i.e., monovalent cation concentration, divalent cation concentration, etc) rather than the tm / salt correction _methods_. There is no reference to the method used to calculate tm or salt corrections in thal.c/h, which is the piece of the primer3 code responsible for the heterodimer / homodimer / hairpin calculations. It appears that those parameters only apply to tm calculation (calcTm) which is instrumented in oligotm.c/h. You could reach out to the primer3 team for further clarification, but from what I can tell the current primer3 library does not support specifying the salt correction method or tm calculation method for the heterodimer / homodimer / hairpin calculations. ",{},,User,False
