11657,IssueCommentEvent,2016-05-06 15:45:02+00:00,5888353,spotify/luigi,2091885,daveFNbuck,251374,spotify,144936161,217479979,"The code for updating graphs is in processHashChange in visualiserApp.js. The code for filtering the task list on the server side is in searchTerm in luigi.js. Before doing auto-refresh, we'll need to do work to enable manual refresh. Right now, if you hit refresh you lose a lot of state. We'll need to update URLs and do page changes to reflect selections and enable things like refresh and hitting back.

We'll also need to update the way dependency graphs refresh. Right now if I hit ""Hide Done"" while waiting for a very large graph to load, I'll quickly get the version I want, then later when the big one finishes loading it'll overwrite the one I was looking at. This can be very frustrating when combined with the lack of memory in the refresh. If we're constantly refreshing, we'll need to ensure that we're not building up a queue of constantly reprocessed graphs.

It might also be worth considering incremental updates in the visualizer. It can take several seconds to do a full refresh when you have a few thousand pending tasks, just to find the state changes for a handful of jobs.",{},,User,False
