11825,IssueCommentEvent,2015-12-11 14:54:58+00:00,38744670,zalando/patroni,339913,alexeyklyukin,1564818,zalando,121577672,163955661,"Patroni expects to connect to the address/port PostgreSQL listens to (the server listen_addresses, configured via the ""postgresql"" section ""listen"" parameter) and postgres database without the password. Basically, if you running patroni on the same host as PostgreSQL itself, you can add 127.0.0.1 as the first address in the list of listen addresses (i.e. ""127.0.0.1,1.2.3.4.5:5432"") (or set it to *), and only enable trust  for 127.0.0.1 connections.

Unfortunately, it looks like we don't support Patroni talking to PostgreSQL via a local socket connection ATM, but this is something we are willing to fix in the future. 
",{},,User,False
11826,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-17 08:08:50+00:00,38744670,zalando/patroni,3407345,CyberDem0n,1564818,zalando,274087040,345173693,"```yaml
postgresql:
 connect_address: localhost:5432
 #changed /var/lib/postgresql/data/postgresql0 to /var/lib/postgresql/10/data/postgresql0 after upgrade rest all are same
 data_dir: /var/lib/postgresql/data/postgresql0
```

Very strange setup...
Do you really run a single zookeeper node?
Are there any other nodes in Patroni cluster?
But anyway, such message `INFO: waiting for leader to bootstrap` could mean only one: your data directory `/var/lib/postgresql/10/data/postgresql0` doesn't exist or empty",{},MEMBER,User,False
