12349,IssueCommentEvent,2016-05-30 22:43:53+00:00,18188537,dronekit/dronekit-python,7077857,peterbarker,12973369,dronekit,157553351,222562622,"On Mon, 30 May 2016, Lorenz Meier wrote:

> @tridge This sounds like it could be a MAVLink 2.0 related issue.

This was related.  dronekit-python was monky-patching a function in 
dronekit - badly.  When that function started receiving keyword arguments, 
dronekit-python started to fail (the dronekit-python function doesn't take 
keyword arguments, so passing thenm in causes failure).

The patch to fix this is already in dronekit-python's head.  No new 
release has been done.

There's currently also an issue some other people are seeing which has 
much the same symptoms.  Somehow people are getting the master version of 
dronekit-python but a release version of SITL.  Haven't gotten to the 
bottom of that yet,

",{},,User,False
