13145,IssueCommentEvent,2016-06-14 13:37:19+00:00,2527828,getsentry/raven-python,3322287,chris-erickson,1396951,getsentry,19560543,225882888,"I eventually found the problem, and it had to do with the git commit integration.  Originally, I was using:

```python
'release': raven.fetch_git_sha(os.path.dirname(__file__)),
```
which worked for months.  It was unable to find a git repo at that location any longer.  It doesn't exist at the same directory as `settings.py` but git commands used to (and should) work anywhere below the git repo directory.  To resolve this, I just changed to:

```python
'release': raven.fetch_git_sha(DJANGO_ROOT),
```
and we're back in business.",{},,User,False
