13195,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-16 19:16:19+00:00,58705171,opencobra/memote,1740827,draeger,2708410,opencobra,269013119,381717750,"@BenjaSanchez this looks very good!

Maybe [SBTab](https://sbtab.net) could be a good solution for a git-based community reconstruction project. It is compatible with the standard format [SBML](http://sbml.org) but can be stored in simple CSV files (or TSV) that people can edit in their table calculation software of choice. For Excel, there is even an addon that imports and exports SBML directly. This format is row-based and can, therefore, work with line-based version control systems, such as git. And, it is much easier to edit than the XML-based formats.",{},NONE,User,False
