13325,IssueCommentEvent,2016-09-10 14:19:19+00:00,4637221,powerline/powerline,322097,ZyX-I,10100576,powerline,176173888,246114187,"It is only tmux which controls redraw time, not powerline or something else. Powerline configuration files tell tmux to redraw every two seconds and additionally tmux will redraw status line in any case on some events. I would first try `tmux set-environment -g POWERLINE_COMMAND echo`, this should make it sure that powerline itself is not related (this should make tmux display arguments of powerline command instead of using powerline). Second try tmux default config with something in `status-right` and `status-interval 2`.

And, in any case, PuTTY native scrollback is not a thing you should use with tmux, tmux has its own scrollback. With my configuration tmux even runs in altscreen which automatically disables scrollback in all terminals I know, including tmux itself (I mean, app that uses altscreen while in tmux will disable scrollback in copy mode for the pane it is used in for the time while it is in altscreen, not some more general problem with scrollback).",{},,User,False
