14122,IssueCommentEvent,2017-05-09 02:20:10+00:00,55808787,openthread/openthread,19217991,librasungirl,16142269,openthread,226936963,300042833,"Thanks @thcu-gp for pointing out the test issues. 
The issue is because that when the dst is ML-EID, according to the select source rules, either RLOC or ML-EID would be selected as source. And OT core would drop the received CoAP message with ML-EID as source.
I will submit a separate PR to explicitly specify RLOC as the source address for CoAP client messages in core to fix the issue.
Additionally, we may need to confirm with other stack vendors to ensure they don't take ML-EID as both source and dest for certification tests. Let's discuss this within ThreadGroup. Thanks.",{},,User,False
14129,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-05 17:44:46+00:00,55808787,openthread/openthread,17729664,abtink,16142269,openthread,233625628,306255112,"@mstamer, thanks for addressing this. I am very much in favor of this (was considering doing this actually).

I have a proposal/suggestion regarding this.

We have two different header files where the settings/configuration options can be defined, the `openthread-config.h` which may be generated by autoconf/`configure.ac` and then we can have a project specific configuration header file given by `OPENTHREAD_PROJECT_CORE_CONFIG_FILE` (with default settings in `""openthread-core-default-config.h""`). We need to ensure all Openthread source files include both. 

We already have a private include file named, `""openthread-core-config.h""` (where we have the #ifdef for the project core config).  My suggestion is to that we update this file and use this as the main setting/configuration related header file for internal OpenThread use. Basically we can add the other #ifdef for `openthread-config.h` in the same file `""openthread-core-config.h""`:
```
 #define OPENTHREAD_CORE_CONFIG_H_IN
 
+#ifdef OPENTHREAD_CONFIG_FILE
+#include OPENTHREAD_CONFIG_FILE
+#else
+#include <openthread-config.h>
+#endif
+
 #ifdef OPENTHREAD_PROJECT_CORE_CONFIG_FILE
 #include OPENTHREAD_PROJECT_CORE_CONFIG_FILE
 #endif

```
We can then include the `""openthread-core-config.h""` at the top of every private/local `hpp` file. Since every `cpp` file includes its corresponding `hpp` file before any other header file, we always have the config/setting header file before any other code everywhere. I feel this makes the internal use much simpler and less error-prone.
For OpenThread public C header files (under `include\`), for now we can continue using the current/existing model.

Thoughts?",{},,User,False
14135,IssueCommentEvent,2016-06-20 15:44:27+00:00,55808787,openthread/openthread,16142208,jwhui,16142269,openthread,160544013,227181624,Fixed in #173.,{},,User,False
14140,IssueCommentEvent,2016-11-01 04:52:10+00:00,55808787,openthread/openthread,16142208,jwhui,16142269,openthread,186456013,257488442,"A non-Commissioner needs to always send the Pending Dataset as a complete dataset (i.e. assumes that the Leader will not copy TLVs from the Active Dataset).  If a Thread device only wants to update selected TLVs, then it needs to operate as a Commissioner and send the MGMT_PENDING_SET to the Leader, so that the Leader can fill in the rest of the (unchanged) TLVs.",{},,User,False
