14153,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-04 17:10:15+00:00,55808787,openthread/openthread,16142208,jwhui,16142269,openthread,163702141,230329227,"@GiedriusM, MLE packets do not have MAC enabled, but instead have security enabled at the MLE layer.  Since MLE is part of the UDP payload, the tag should be included in the IPv6 and UDP length values.  What's happening here is that the MLE implementation is stripping off the tag after security processing and then the modified packet is being delivered to the host after MLE processing is done.

In general, processed MLE packets should probably not be exported to the host.  `wpantund` is just dropping them anyway, as you noted above.",{},,User,False
