14183,IssueCommentEvent,2015-07-07 23:53:53+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,1743873,mateor,3065172,pantsbuild,90558165,119376607,"Shoot, I was out of town for a week meant to return to this sooner. The oldre ivysettings.xml had special ""tweaked"" resolvers that were specifically put in place to support SNAPSHOT-style artifacts. As such they resolve every time and so the jar would never be pulled into the ivy cache (causing a similar problem). My intuition on this is that there is still a copy of the resolver in your ivy cache. If you can share it a -ldebug run would probably be the next step. I want to ping @jsirois who is far more familiar with this process than I and will surely be a big help. Sorry for the long wait!",{},,User,False
