14259,IssueCommentEvent,2016-11-28 23:39:25+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,46740,stuhood,3065172,pantsbuild,190588248,263430445,"While the new test is very useful, I worry that this is not hooked up completely from end-to-end. In particular, an integration test with a subproject is probably a blocker for landing this.

I'd recommend creating an integration test like: https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/blob/f3f6f012f7f43c2f4632e12b103362dd399b4560/tests/python/pants_test/engine/legacy/test_changed_integration.py ... and create a tiny anonymous subdirectory below another working copy.

Two potential approaches for the test:
1. Create a subproject under the `pantsbuild/pants` repo (say, under `testprojects`) and then have the integration test use options that declare the project temporarily. You might possibly need to ignore the BUILD files in this subdirectory.
2. Have the integration test create two anonymous ""repos"" in the test, nested within one another.",{},,User,False
