14292,IssueCommentEvent,2016-04-27 08:57:58+00:00,7347535,pimusicbox/mopidy-musicbox-webclient,934824,kingosticks,11539267,pimusicbox,150654192,215017415,"You know you can have multiple branches and rebase your other branches on develop after this is merged, right? 

I've not had enough time to go through the diff as it's big and it affects the playtrack functions which are historically difficult to get right. One thing I noticed was that you did seem to remove the special PLAY_ALL case for a stream. This one might seem odd but it's actually surprisingly useful behaviour if you try and use it. Am I right this has now gone? ",{},,User,False
14293,IssueCommentEvent,2016-02-15 18:39:05+00:00,7347535,pimusicbox/mopidy-musicbox-webclient,10268911,jcass77,11539267,pimusicbox,113995858,184341459,"This appears to be a known issue (see: https://github.com/mopidy/mopidy-youtube/issues/34).

It might be better to track it as part of the Mopidy-Youtube project as I doubt there is much that can be done in the web client to improve this situation.",{},,User,False
14294,IssueCommentEvent,2016-03-10 11:12:24+00:00,7347535,pimusicbox/mopidy-musicbox-webclient,10268911,jcass77,11539267,pimusicbox,67943710,194795000,"I'm not quite sure how one would go about implementing this cleanly and in a way that will be portable across all backends.

At the moment, the options are to use one of the following methods to build the tracklist:
- ``LibraryController.browse`` - provides a listing of items contained in the URI root, but not recursively as far as I know.
- ``LibraryController.search`` - it may be possible to call this with e.g. ``{uris=['file:///MusicBox']}``, but not all backends support searching.

These are just some initial thoughts...
",{},,User,False
