14930,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-31 13:14:10+00:00,3470471,FortAwesome/Font-Awesome,556268,tagliala,1505683,FortAwesome,345524329,409216281,"@GedMarc sorry, maybe I didn't get this issue correctly

> If solid overwrites the fa4 icons, what is the purpose of the v4shim?

v4shims are intended to update Font Awesome 4 to Font Awesome 5. It is not intended to make FA4 and FA5 work side by side. You should remove FA4's stylesheet and use FA5's ones

Take another look at the docs: https://fontawesome.com/how-to-use/on-the-web/setup/upgrading-from-version-4

Could you please fill up a bug request that follows our [bug report template](https://github.com/FortAwesome/Font-Awesome/issues/new?template=bug-report.md)

A reproducible test would help us in understand the issue.",{},MEMBER,User,False
