15080,IssueCommentEvent,2018-08-02 14:54:34+00:00,27888295,SatelliteQE/nailgun,13135483,sean797,8754276,SatelliteQE,344747617,409955485,"@abalakh I'm thinking we should leave it as is - thanks.

> @sean797 btw that's why we always ask for test results - despite your change right now is trivial one-linear, unfortunately it won't work due to reasons described above.

As a maintainer, it's your job, as well as the contributor, to test changes. Relying on the contributor to post the output of his or her tests is mostly useless. You have no reason to trust the contributors' tests, how do you know there isn't something environmental to the contributor that is making it work? This is especially relevant with a library like Nailgun that could be used across many different Foreman, Katello or Satellite versions. I suggested a far better approach in https://github.com/SatelliteQE/nailgun/pull/504#issuecomment-405891723

