15324,IssueCommentEvent,2015-11-04 11:25:14+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,98387,marcan,9289019,letsencrypt,77849129,153691268,"It would be nice if the plugin could be passed the name of the domain (or list of domains) as part of the restart() method, or have some other function invoked to notify of the changed certs. I'm writing a simple plugin that just shells out to a shell script for authentication requests, so that you can easily integrate it with custom server configs. This includes multiple server types, e.g. the shell script could know how to update certs for nginx, icecast, and postfix, for example.

