15375,IssueCommentEvent,2016-02-23 09:23:26+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,482089,domcleal,9289019,letsencrypt,135553013,187617295,"The parse error's from the line breaks and continuations within the `<VirtualHost>` blocks, e.g.

<pre>
<VirtualHost \
    0.0.0.0:7080 \
    [00000:000:000:0000::2]:7080 \
    0.0.0.0:7080 \
    127.0.0.1:7080 \
    >
</pre>

If you remove the _last_ `\` and put the closing `>` on the same line and after `127.0.0.1:7080` then it'll work around the problem.  You can put it back after running the LE client I think.

I've fixed the problem in Augeas and will file a PR for LE shortly.",{},,User,False
