15401,IssueCommentEvent,2015-11-29 06:58:49+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,4323539,TheNavigat,9289019,letsencrypt,117966539,160387956,"This issue looks a bit too convoluted for a volunteer, but here are my 2 cents, for anyone who'd like to work on this.

The message is displayed in https://github.com/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/blob/master/letsencrypt/cli.py#L153.

```regr``` is defined in https://github.com/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/blob/master/letsencrypt/client.py#L118, it's returned from ```perform_registration``` function, https://github.com/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/blob/master/letsencrypt/client.py#L153

And then there's also ```regr``` in https://github.com/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/blob/master/acme/acme/client.py#L103, returned from https://github.com/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/blob/master/acme/acme/client.py#L65.

One parameter sent to the initialization method of ```regr``` is ```response```, https://github.com/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/blob/master/acme/acme/client.py#L97, which is the return value of the ```self.net.post``` method. ```self.net``` is a ```ClientNetwork``` object, initialized here. https://github.com/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/blob/master/acme/acme/client.py#L56. The ClientNetwork class, https://github.com/letsencrypt/letsencrypt/blob/master/acme/acme/client.py#L478, basically sends a request to Let's Encrypt server and one of the returned parameters is basically the ToS URL.

It's a bit too convoluted because the system is a bit too robust. I'm not sure how to carefully remove the URL part and replace it with the content of the ToS page, not sure where to start.",{},,User,False
15403,IssueCommentEvent,2015-10-27 18:22:15+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,2334868,ntdaley,9289019,letsencrypt,49832962,151598700,"FranBar:

