15494,IssueCommentEvent,2017-09-09 07:13:37+00:00,79083614,python-trio/trio,609896,njsmith,26335827,python-trio,255208133,328260062,"> `remove = __all__.remove`

ughhhh this solution is so terrible and so beautiful in different ways.

I guess if that's what we have to do then that's what we have to do. I'm really curious if this fiddling helps with other IDEs. And wish we had a better way to test this. It's seems very likely that PyCharm will someday get cleverer about these, but will it be because it becomes clever enough not to need this tricks, or clever enough to see through our tricks and break everything again? It is a mystery 👻 

