15806,IssueCommentEvent,2016-06-04 00:32:59+00:00,4744355,soft-matter/trackpy,2985325,nkeim,5857177,soft-matter,151215250,223724571,"There is a separation parameter in Blair-Dufresne but it is applied after peak-finding, not after calculating the centroids. So that is a minor difference. I think that it is better to apply it at the end (as in this PR), because if two ""features"" are part of the same extended feature, they will migrate toward each other during refinement, making them more likely to get culled.

I would like to do the comparison one more time before merge and observe how the output has/hasn't changed. I can probably do that this weekend.

So will the next release of trackpy be v0.4? I think that is an appropriate increment when a core algorithm is altered.",{},,User,False
