15996,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-05 23:01:00+00:00,12407457,Exa-Networks/exabgp,24572,chantra,5339170,Exa-Networks,261874854,334615258,"ok, even simpler wait to reproduce.... instead of running `bird` on the other end, you can just run:

```
nc -l -p 179
```

basically, TCP connection get established, OPEN get sent and we busy loop waiting to read from the peer.

I tried setting `open.bgp.openwait` to something low like `2`, hoping that we would get the busy spin for 2 sec and then it would stop until the next connection establishes, but it was still taking 100% CPU.

For now, I can narrow this down to https://github.com/Exa-Networks/exabgp/blob/master/lib/exabgp/reactor/peer.py#L323

It is unclear to me if this is the original issue, but this is definitely something that can contribute to it :)",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
