There will be even a tagged release candidate 1 for GC 2.0 in the next weeks (the current goal is still ""within January""), therefore you can either wait or update another it again.

> However I could add a gnu-cobol-svn package for those who want the latest revision.

Sounds reasonable in any case. But I thing this should add the dependency flex and bison which are needed to rebuild some files which currently are in svn (will be kicked out someday) but aren't always updated - if you've added bison and flex as prerequisites you could do ``cd cobc && rm -f parser.c pplex.c ppparse.c scanner.c 2>/dev/null`` to force regeneration of these files.",{},,User,False
