16257,IssueCommentEvent,2017-07-19 12:45:30+00:00,692654,python-babel/flask-babel,3081375,DonnchaC,14215782,python-babel,244017995,316374230,"Sorry, it looks like this behavior is intentional in Jinja. The Jinja Babel extension explicitly converts `gettext` result values to Markup objects which are treated as safe (https://github.com/pallets/jinja/blob/e605ff1a0bc304bb543f6867c0798e0480f31926/jinja2/ext.py#L142).  IMO this is under-documented and there should at least be an option to allow gettext results to be treated as unsafe in Jinja.

I'll open an issue on the Jinja2 repo. Feel free to close this.
 ",{},,User,False
16260,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-03 10:50:56+00:00,57372073,python-hyper/h11,609896,njsmith,13035907,python-hyper,310700559,378208888,"Oh, heh, nice catch!

It looks like that was originally written by @jseabold and contributed to statsmodels, in this commit: https://github.com/statsmodels/statsmodels/commit/24c850c62fd1716ca070a03b35734c71b2ffcae1#diff-01b20d9015b8f6f5ab9a901553c96a51

So I guess that means it's [licensed under BSD3](https://github.com/statsmodels/statsmodels/blob/master/LICENSE.txt).

This most recently came from my project [patsy](https://github.com/pydata/patsy), but I guess the Debian devs managing the python-patsy package missed it.",{},OWNER,User,False
