16700,IssueCommentEvent,2016-10-18 17:44:30+00:00,46374199,IntelRealSense/librealsense,6958867,dorodnic,14095512,IntelRealSense,183681831,254584178,"Hi,
librealsense does not include any record and playback capabilities at this moment. 
Some work on recording and playback functionality on top of librealsense has been done in [RealSense Linux SDK](https://github.com/IntelRealSense/realsense_sdk), however I fear it is not quite what you are looking for (to the best of my knowledge it uses a different format and currently only available on Linux right now). 
While simple recording and playback is not necessarily out of scope of librealsense, XDM is a proprietary format so it would be complicated to support it. ",{},,User,False
16703,IssueCommentEvent,2018-08-01 08:34:44+00:00,46374199,IntelRealSense/librealsense,8899900,jb455,14095512,IntelRealSense,342315254,409496447,"Hi,
I was using the depth stream in a software device in C#, not sure if that's relevant. I couldn't reproduce it just turning the stream off and on in realsense viewer, or opening and closing the app; but the error was coming up if I opened it up in my app a couple of times first then opened viewer.
The basic flow of my app is:

1. Query devices, select D410
2. Query streams, select desired depth stream
3. Set stream options (depth units, visual preset)
4. Use `Sensor.Open(StreamProfile)` and `Sensor.Start(FrameQueue)` to start the stream
5. `Frame = FrameQueue.WaitForFrame()` to get frames; copying data bytes & some other properties to pass to software sensor
6. `Dispose` frame when not needed any more in each loop
7. Call `StreamProfile.Dispose()`, `Sensor.Stop()`, `Sensor.Close()` when camera not needed any more.

Going through this whole process several times is what was causing the issue.",{},NONE,User,False
