16707,IssueCommentEvent,2017-12-13 05:47:24+00:00,46374199,IntelRealSense/librealsense,6958867,dorodnic,14095512,IntelRealSense,281167860,351289955,"Glad to hear it worked!

As a random guess I would try to explore USB settings in BIOS. On some boards the auto-detection is not working very well, and you can explicitly specify USB3 preference. Unfortunately, I don't really have a good reference for this, just from personal experience with some of the machines at the office. 

The firmware update protocol for Intel RealSense is somewhat proprietary while the SDK is open-source, so we can't bundle them together. However, with large number of engineering-samples out there we acknowledge the need for such tool. It is now being validated and is scheduled to be released soon for Windows and Linux. Once published we will link to it from GitHub documentation. 
If you can reach out to the Intel representatives who provided you the camera, they can most-likely send you pre-release software. ",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
