16921,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-31 17:38:47+00:00,13592924,python-openxml/python-docx,2062718,scanny,3403760,python-openxml,269887103,340842841,"No, there is no API support for this operation yet. This is a tricky operation for a few reasons. 

First, any external references (like hyperlinks or images) from any cells that will be deleted need to be resolved first, so they're not left dangling.

Second, merged cells must be interpreted to work out what the result of deleting the column should be. This might just be ""shortening"" the merged cell from say 3-cells to 2-cells, or it could be deleting the first cell, which may mean also deleting the contents of the cell, leaving it blank.

In any case, it's an interesting feature, just not trivial to specify and implement.",{},NONE,User,False
