17183,IssueCommentEvent,2017-02-15 06:59:29+00:00,66823715,intel-analytics/BigDL,2551195,i8run,10941215,intel-analytics,207463380,279932415,"Hi Jaymahesh,

For Q1, the **model_file** is the model have been saved somewhere. So
+   How to generate the model ?

    ```
    ./dist/bin/bigdl.sh -- \
    spark-submit --class com.intel.analytics.bigdl.models.vgg.Train \
    dist/lib/bigdl-0.1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar \
    --core physical_core_number \
    --node node_number \
    --env spark \
    -f Cifar-folder \
    -b batchsize \
    --checkpoint ~/model
    ```

    This command will generate the model you want under *model* which is controlled by `--checkpoint` .

+   How to load the model ?

    ```
    ./dist/bin/bigdl.sh -- \
    spark-submit --class com.intel.analytics.bigdl.models.vgg.Test \
    dist/lib/bigdl-0.1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies-all-in-one.jar \
    -f cifar-folder \
    --model model_file \
    --nodeNumber node_number \
    --core physical_core_number \
    --env spark \
    -b batch_size
    ```

    This command will load the model generated by the command above, which is controlled by `--model`.

For Q2, Does the **log** means *the loss of every iteration/epoch* ? If so,
+   Loss info was printed on **stdout** where you submit the job.  You can use Linux command `nohup`, `tee` or some other IO redirection method to save  the log.

+   Other intermediate file is under the path specified by `--checkpoint` .

+   And currently, we don't support visualize the loss/accuracy. Maybe you can use `gnuplot` with a little scripts to visualize it.

     ",{},,User,False
