17248,IssueCommentEvent,2015-03-09 22:35:09+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,517546,tiborsimko,1157480,inveniosoftware,60099271,77959203,"> Not increasing the barrier for contributions (which is already quite high) is indeed a good thing in my opinion. 

Wouldn't this concern be addressed by providing `kwalitee` tool that people run locally on their branches to see authoritative and comprehensive report on what's recommended to fix in their branches?  

At first try, the occasional contributors may see the kwalitee observations as funny-sounding perhaps, but if the report is comprehensive and all-encompassing, then people are also handed clear path to improvement, a kind of authoritative ""learning aid"".

(Note: currently the kwalitee tool may ""overdo"" or ""underdo"" certain warnings, but we plan on improving it constantly.  E.g. for `master` the PEP-8 is only recommended, so `invenio-check-branch` only shows kwalitee warnings brought by the new feature branch itself.  We can configure `kwalitee` in similar way so that its output would be fully authoritative in similar manner, based on agreed coding standards in each concrete project.)",{},,User,False
