17683,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-13 17:05:58+00:00,49976939,learningequality/kolibri,7193975,christianmemije,3926525,learningequality,234962308,308183594,"A few issues with having two separate views for username and password. A username does not have feedback on the username they just entered when are sent to the password view. There is no way to change username once inputted. 


If you enter a username then an incorrect password, you are sent back to the username view (even though it might just be an incorrect password.) Having both fields visible would allow the user to quickly see what mistake they likely committed. Btw, clicking on the sign in button after getting sent back to the username, does not proceed to the password field. (Bug)


I think it would be better if both fields were visible (show password field below username if not a learner), or have indication of username and allow navigation between username and password views. The former seems easier.",{},,User,False
