18247,IssueCommentEvent,2016-06-20 17:47:03+00:00,11852493,GoogleCloudPlatform/compute-image-packages,677960,dmichel1,2810941,GoogleCloudPlatform,160954485,227216097,"We don't use the Ubuntu images provided by Google.

To give you some context into my environment we build GCE images off our internal image that we use for bare-metal installations. It's essentially a tar-ball containing a run of `debootstrap minimum` for Ubuntu 14.04 and a run of puppet which configures the rest of the OS. That tar-ball is then pulled into our GCE image build process where we apply Google specific configurations. 

I'm actually looking into removing cloud-init as a dependency in our images, as the new guest  specifically the `google-compute-engine` package does 90% of the job (startup/shutdown scripts, ssh keys, etc). The only requirement missing for us is disk resizing during boot which we can work around. 

